# =============================================================================
# Crêpe Time Tunisia — Backend Environment Variables
# =============================================================================
# Copy to .env and fill with real values. NEVER commit .env or real secrets.
# =============================================================================

# Supabase — REQUIRED
# Project URL: https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
# Service Role Key (Settings > API) — backend only, bypasses RLS
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_service_role_key_here

# JWT — Use a long random string (e.g. openssl rand -hex 32)
JWT_SECRET_KEY=your_jwt_secret_here

# URLs
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:5173
BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:5000

# Google OAuth — also set in Supabase Dashboard (Authentication > Providers > Google)
# Optional in .env; Supabase uses Dashboard values for signInWithOAuth
GOOGLE_ID=your_google_client_id.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_SECRET=GOCSPX-your_client_secret

# Cloudinary (Image Upload) — cloudinary.com Dashboard
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your_cloud_name
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=your_api_key
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=your_api_secret

# =============================================================================
# WhatsApp Business API (Meta Graph API v20)
# =============================================================================
#
# HOW THE SYSTEM WORKS
# ─────────────────────
# Two-channel notification on every order:
#
#  Channel A — Meta Business API (automatic, server-side)
#    • Sends full order details directly to the restaurant WhatsApp  ← no client click needed
#    • Sends a confirmation receipt to the customer's WhatsApp        ← if phone provided
#    • Requires WHATSAPP_API_TOKEN + WHATSAPP_API_PHONE_ID below
#
#  Channel B — wa.me deep-link (manual fallback)
#    • Always generated and returned to the browser
#    • Browser opens WhatsApp with the order pre-filled in the chat
#    • Used automatically if Channel A is not configured or fails
#
# =============================================================================
# STEP-BY-STEP: HOW TO GET YOUR CREDENTIALS
# =============================================================================
#
# PREREQUISITES
#   • A Facebook / Meta Business account
#   • A verified Facebook Business (business.facebook.com)
#   • A phone number that is NOT already registered on WhatsApp
#     (use a dedicated SIM card for the restaurant, e.g. +21625799066)
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 1 — Create a Meta Developer App
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   1. Go to https://developers.facebook.com
#   2. Click "My Apps" → "Create App"
#   3. Select "Business" as the app type
#   4. Fill in the app name (e.g. "Crepe Time Notifications") and contact email
#   5. Click "Create App"
#
# STEP 2 — Add the WhatsApp Product
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   1. In your new app dashboard, click "Add Product"
#   2. Find "WhatsApp" and click "Set up"
#   3. You will now be in the "WhatsApp > Getting Started" section
#
# STEP 3 — Link your Business Manager
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   1. Under "WhatsApp > Getting Started", click "Add a phone number"
#   2. Select your WhatsApp Business Account (WABA) from your Business Manager
#      — If you do not have one yet, create it at business.facebook.com
#   3. Accept the Terms of Service
#
# STEP 4 — Register your Restaurant Phone Number
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   1. In "WhatsApp > Phone Numbers", click "Add phone number"
#   2. Enter the restaurant number in E.164 format: +21625799066
#   3. Verify via SMS or voice call
#   4. Copy the "Phone Number ID" shown — this is WHATSAPP_API_PHONE_ID
#      Example: 123456789012345
#
# STEP 5 — Generate a Permanent Access Token
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   The "Temporary Token" shown in the Getting Started tab expires in 24 hours.
#   For production you need a SYSTEM USER TOKEN:
#
#   a. Go to business.facebook.com → Settings → System Users
#   b. Click "Add" → name it "crepetime-backend" → role: Admin
#   c. Click "Generate New Token"
#   d. Select your app, set expiration to "Never"
#   e. Tick the permission: "whatsapp_business_messaging"
#   f. Click Generate → Copy the token → this is WHATSAPP_API_TOKEN
#
# STEP 6 — Set Env Vars
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   Fill in the three variables below and restart the backend.
#
# STEP 7 — Test
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   • On the Meta Developer dashboard (WhatsApp > API Setup) you can send a
#     test message to any number you add as a test recipient.
#   • Place a test order on your site — the backend logs will show:
#       [WhatsApp] ✓ Restaurant notified — order #XXXXXXXX
#       [WhatsApp] ✓ Customer confirmation sent to +2137XXXXXXX
#   • If you see errors, check: token expiry, phone number verification status,
#     and that the WABA is in "Live" mode (not "Development").
#
# STEP 8 — Go Live (remove 24h sandbox limit)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   In Development mode (default) you can only message numbers added as
#   "test recipients". To message ANY number:
#   1. In App Dashboard → App Review → Request permissions
#   2. Request: "whatsapp_business_messaging"
#   3. Submit for review (takes 1-5 business days)
#   Once approved, your app is in Live mode — no restrictions.
#
# IMPORTANT NOTES
#   • WhatsApp Business API is free up to 1,000 service conversations/month
#   • System User tokens tied to an Admin do NOT expire unless revoked
#   • Keep WHATSAPP_API_TOKEN secret — treat it like a database password
#   • Never commit .env to git
#
# =============================================================================

# Restaurant WhatsApp number (E.164 format — no spaces)
WHATSAPP_RESTAURANT_PHONE=+21625799066

# From Step 5 above — System User Token with whatsapp_business_messaging
WHATSAPP_API_TOKEN=

# From Step 4 above — Phone Number ID (NOT the phone number itself)
WHATSAPP_API_PHONE_ID=

# Resend (used by Supabase Edge Function notify-client, not backend)
# Set via: supabase secrets set RESEND_API_KEY=re_your_key
# RESEND_API_KEY=re_your_key_here
